Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/withdraws
Object: Relates an act of withdrawal to the made available thing being withdrawn.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/madeAvailableOn
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to a House, to the date on which they are made available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/madeAvailableFrom
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to the organisation making those materials available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/OrganisationAccountableToParliament
Object: An organisation accountable to Parliament: being a Government department, a Government organisation, a non-governmental organisation with a duty to answer questions or an organisation with a duty to lay papers.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/
Object: A model describing the act of making material available to a House and any subsequent withdrawal.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/MakingAvailable
Object: The act of making materials available to a House or to a House by means of its Library.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/WithdrawnThing
Object: A thing having been withdrawn from a House.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/MadeAvailableThing
Object: A thing made available to a House or to a House by means of its Library.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/makesAvailable
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to the thing made available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/withdrawnByIncumbency
Object: Relates an act of withdrawal to the incumbency of a person in a position performing the withdrawal.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/toHouse
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to a House, to the House in which they are made available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/Withdrawal
Object: The act of withdrawing a thing previously made available to a House or to a House by means of its Library.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/intoSession
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to a House, to the session into which they are made available. Material laid during a prorogation is considered laid into the following session.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/duringSession
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to a House, to the session in which they are made available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/withdrawnByOrganisation
Object: Relates an act of withdrawal to the organisation performing the withdrawal.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/withdrawnOn
Object: Relates an act of withdrawal, to the date on which the thing is withdrawn.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/resultsIn
Object: Relates an act of withdrawal to the thing having been withdrawn.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/Incumbency
Object: The holding of a position by a person, including the time period for which this was the case. For example, Philip Hammond holding the position of Foreign Secretary between two dates.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/Session
Object: A period during which Parliament is able to conduct business on days of its choosing. A session is within a Parliament period. The first session of a Parliament begins on the same day as the Parliament period and ends on a day named in a subsequent prorogation proclamation. Subsequent sessions within the Parliament period begin and end on dates named in subsequent prorogation proclamations. The final session of a Parliament ends either with prorogation followed by dissolution or with dissolution. Session periods are the same for both Houses.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/madeAvailableBy
Object: Relates an act of making materials available to a House, to incumbency of a person in a position making those materials available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/making-available/House
Object: A parliamentary House, for example: the House of Lords.
